    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "treating len-1 list and scalar group-ands the same is a long standing design decision and makes for nicer code. what you are proposing is actually very confusing as now you would have to explicity unbox things when iterating, now you can simply\r\n\r\n```\r\nfor name1, data in df.groupby('a').groups\r\nfor (name1, name2), data in df.groupby(['a', 'b']).groups\r\n```\r\nare pretty common idioms\r\n\r\nyou are suggesting that the first would be\r\n```\r\nfor (name, ), data in df.groupby('a').groups\r\n```\r\nwhich is very odd"
  },
