    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I completely agree with your argument. But I was hoping it is possible to leave `df.groupby('a')` behavior unchanged, while changing the `df.groupby(['a'])` behavior.\r\n\r\nMy rationale is that single-element lists would only occur when someone is programmatically passing a list (of presumably unknown length), and in that case the current behavior requires, at best, the workaround  below (and at worst, a debugging session followed by the workaround below):\r\n\r\n```\r\nfor names, data in df.groupby(my_columns).groups:\r\n  if len(my_columns) == 1:\r\n    names = [names]\r\n  for name in names:\r\n    do_stuff(name, data)\r\n```\r\n"
  },
